<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FD0FE5E48A7564FFE2BFCF7" pageId="414" pageNumber="415" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FD0FE5E48A7564FFDA5FD14" blockId="414.[151,1436,355,920]" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD0FE5E48A7564FFE3CFE8C" bold="true" box="[151,409,355,380]" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">Description of female</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FD0FE5E4A585648FD66FE8B" box="[616,707,356,380]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="414" pageNumber="415" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. Head brown-reddish or black-brown, except mandible, clypeus and anterior region of face yellow; antenna brown, except segments 1–3 yellow; pronotum brown-reddish or blackbrown; rest of mesosoma black or black-brown; metasoma brown; legs testaceous. Antenna clavate. Head (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FD0FE5E4D545680FF70FE17" captionStart="PLATE 129" captionStartId="412.[151,233,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[251,1360,292,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-100@412.[151,1436,267,1919]" captionTargetPageId="412" captionText="PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">Plate 129D</figureCitation>
) weakly excavated, shiny, smooth, unsculptured; occipital carina absent. Palpal formula 5/2. Pronotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum shiny, sculptured by some longitudinal keels. Metanotum short, about as long as scutellum, not hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, with anterior surface unsculptured and posterior surface transversely striate. Mesopleuron not transversely striate. Metapleuron transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture obsolete. Segment 1 of protarsus slightly shorter than segment 4 (9:10). Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FD0FE5E4A2255A8FD2EFD6C" box="[530,651,644,668]" captionStart="PLATE 129" captionStartId="412.[151,233,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[251,1360,292,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-100@412.[151,1436,267,1919]" captionTargetPageId="412" captionText="PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">Plate 129E</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and three–six peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FD0FE5E490F558BFE1CFD4F" box="[319,441,679,703]" captionStart="PLATE 129" captionStartId="412.[151,233,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[251,1360,292,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-100@412.[151,1436,267,1919]" captionTargetPageId="412" captionText="PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" pageId="414" pageNumber="415">Plate 129E</figureCitation>
) with inner margin proximally serrated, with one row of 12–13 lamellae; distal apex with 5–7 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
